<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[436,1831,416,940]" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">
<materialsCitation box="[499,1573,745,789]" country="Guam" location="Fullaway" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" specimenCount="1">
This small ant was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1177,745,789]" name="Guam" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Guam</collectingCountry>
by 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0E4F7F497E675A2CB4E4FE24142075F8:833998847E675A2CB1B6FD6D13DF7541" box="[1252,1416,745,789]" country="Guam" name="Fullaway" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Fullaway</location>
in 1911.
</materialsCitation>
We collected what may be this insect in different localities, but the identification is not positive. This ant is known from the West Indies, 
<collectingCountry box="[1301,1463,847,891]" name="Palestine" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Palestine</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1488,1703,847,891]" name="Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1728,1823,847,891]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">India</collectingCountry>
, and Tahiti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
